18. Qc5{ A new move, but I think a logical one. We simply protect  d5 . }( { My good friend Jan Smeets played }18...Be6 19.Rd1 Ne4 { , which is a very interesting pawn sacrifice. To his surprise, his opponent knew all about it and kept blitzing his moves. After }20.Nxe4 dxe4 21.Bxe4 Rxd1+ 22.Qxd1 Rd8 23.Qg1 Qc4 24.Bf3 h6 25.e4 a6 26.Qe1 { , he was probably already worse, which made me think that maybe giving up a second pawn isn't that much fun. Black has to play accurately here, to keep the balance. } )
