4. Bg5( { One of those sidelines that pops up occasionally in the tournament arena. Lines like }4...Nc6 5.Nc3 f6 6.e4!? fxg5 7.exd5 { shows that there are some tricky ideas behind this move, but all in all it's obviously not too worrying. } )
4. f6( 4...Nf6 { would be my choice if White were forced to play }5.Nc3 { , allowing }5...Ne4 { . Unfortunately,   }5.Bxf6 { may lead to a somewhat improved version of the Trompowsky. } )
