9. Nxd4{ Once again the most challenging reply. It turns out we do not need to fear the opening of the long diagonal. }
10. Bxb7{ This pawn turns out to be poisonous. }
10. Qc7( { It's important to start with this move. Instead, }10...Nc2+ 11.Kf1 Qc7 { allows }12.Bc6+ Ke7 13.Bxc5+ { and mate next move! } )
11. Bxa8
11. Nc2+
12. Kf1
12. Nxe3+
13. fxe3
13. Qxe5
14. Bc6+
14. Ke7{ After a long sequence, it's time to take stock. Black is an exchange for a pawn down, but White's position is in ruins. A knight jump to  g4  could prove highly unpleasant, but Black could also play it slow with ... g7 - g6  to fianchetto the bishop and bring the rook to  d8 . }
