7. f3
7. Bb4
8. h4{ Played by GM Lubomir Ftacnik at the end of the eighties, this move carries the rather crude threat of trapping the bishop with  g2 - g4  followed by  h4 - h5 . }
8. c5{ Hitting White in the center, thereby preventing the threat  g2 - g4 . }( { Instead, }8...h6 9.e4 { is the deeper point behind  8.h4 . With the moves   }8.h4 h6 { included, the piece sacrifice }9.e4 Bxe4? 10.fxe4 Nxe4 { , which is how we play against  8.e4 , makes little sense because of }11.Rh3! { and White is just winning. Retreating with   }9...Bh7 { also looked better for White after }10.Bxc4 { in Gelfand-Smagin, Norilsk 1987. } )
