9. Qa5( { The most precise queen move. }9...Qc7 { allows }10.Qd6! { after which Black is forced to take the queens off. Following }10...Qxd6 11.cxd6 Bxd6 12.Nxc4 Bg3+ 13.Kd1 { , matters were far from clear in Korobov-Motylev, Ohrid 2001. White is ready to }{ play  e2 - e4 . } )
10. Qd4{ The threat on  c3  means that White, once again, can not execute the threat of trapping the bishop on  f5  with  g2 - g4 . }
10. Bxc5
11. Qxc4
