14. c4{ Another big move, sacrificing another pawn. Now the threat is ... Bb4 - d6 , pinning and winning the knight. White needs to take on  c4  and has two ways to do so. }
15. Nxc4( { The two games that have reached this position, including the stem game Ding Liren-Caruana, continued with this natural capture. We react differently compared to }15.Bxc4 { . } )
15. Nbd7{ Here we do bring the knight to  d7 , but it won't stay there. In most lines, it will reroute to  f8  and  g6 . }( { Jeffery Xiong played }15...Qc8 { in an online game, but it's not advisable to repeat it. The precise engine sequence }16.Ne3 { ( }16.e5 Bxc3 17.bxc3 Nxd5⇆ { was the game Indjic-Xiong, chess.com 2021, where Black was doing OK.)   }16...Bxc3 17.bxc3 Qxc3 18.Rb1 Nbd7 19.Bb5! Nc5 20.Re1 Ncxe4+ 21.Kf1! { gives White a winning advantage. A lot of things are hanging in Black's camp and }{ the simple  Bc1 - b2  is a threat as well. } )
16. Be3
16. Nf8{ Intending to embarrass the queen on  f4 . }( { It is tempting to make a forceful move like }16...Bxc4 17.Bxc4 Ne5 18.Be2 Bd6 { , but White has a convincing way to parry these threats. Following }19.Qf5 Nc4 20.Bxc4 Re5 21.Qh3 Rh5 22.Qxh5! Nxh5 23.g3 { , White is doing excellent }{ with a rook, bishop, and big central pawns for the queen. } )
17. Bd4{ Very sensible. White vacates the  e3 -square so that the queen may potentially fall back, while the knight on  c4  may also be able to use the freed square. }
17. Rc8( { It's important to start with this move. Caruana mixed up with }17...Ng6 { , after which }18.Qc1 { would have been more or less winning. Ding played }18.Qf5 { , which is less clear, but won anyway. Truly a pity for Caruana to have spoiled his fantastic novelty in this way. } )
18. Nd2{ This retreat gives Black a wide range of options. }
18. Ne6{ Making use of the pin. }
19. dxe6( 19.Bxf6 Qb6+! { shows why we didn't }{ play ... Nf8 - e6  on the previous move. With the knight on  c4 , we don't have the check on  b6 ! }{ Here, }20.Qe3 Bc5 { is decisive. } )
19. Qxd4+
20. Qe3
20. Qxe3+
21. Kxe3
21. Bxe6{ White isn't much going to enjoy the extra pawn! }
