10. Qe2{ A new move! Given that this is a Lifetime Repertoire, I feel we also need to be ready for moves that have not yet been introduced into practice but may well be in the future. }( { White is looking to improve over }10.Qb3 Nxe5 11.dxe5 Nd7 12.e4 Be6 { , which hits the queen }{ on  b3 . }{ After   }10.Qe2 { , the same line }10...Nxe5 11.dxe5 Nd7 12.e4 Be6 { continues with }13.f4! { and a big advantage for White. } )
10. Nxe5
11. dxe5
11. Ne4{ Stopping White from playing  e3 - e4  altogether. }
12. Nxe4
12. Bxe4
13. f3{ An interesting moment: where to move our bishop? }
13. Bf5( { Counterintuitive perhaps, as the bishop will get kicked away from here as well, but after }13...Bg6 14.h4 h5 15.e6! fxe6 16.e4 { , we risk that the bishop is out of the game for a long period of time. } )
14. e4
14. Bd7{ The bishop will temporarily be passive, but temporarily is the key word here. After a future ... b7 - b5 /... c6 - c5 , the bishop is back in the game. We will play ... e7 - e6  next, and develop our  f8 -bishop and castle. I'd already take Black. }
