11. Qf3
11. Bc2( { The endgame after }11...Bg6 12.Qg3 Qxg3 13.hxg3 { is a bit better for White, as two games by Hungarian GM Banusz showed. We place the bishop }{ on  c2 , to get a slightly more favorable version of that endgame. } )
12. Qg3( 12.e4 e5! { already forces White to act with care. } )
