13. O-O
13. Bb4
14. Be3
14. Qe7{ Ni Hua played this already back in 2011, and it was recently picked up in correspondence chess as well. }( { After the obvious }14...O-O 15.Qb3 { , }{ the threat of  Nc3 - a2  is disturbing. Some games continued }15...Qb6 16.Bf2 Bc5!? { , but both }17.Qd1 { and }17.Qc4!? { retain an edge. } )
15. Qb3
15. Rb8{ Now we are all set for  Nc3 - a2 , as  b7  is covered. Also the idea behind  14...Qe7  becomes clear now: we can meet  Be3 - f4  with ... Bb4 - d6 . }
16. Rad1
16. O-O{ A typical Slav position. White has central control but our position is super solid. An idea is to prepare the ... f7 - f5  advance with moves likes ... Kg8 - h8  and ... h7 - h6 . }( { The correspondence game Hehir-Meissner from 2023, was agreed drawn after }17.Bf4 Bd6 18.Bxd6 Qxd6 19.Rd2 Qf4 20.Rfd1 Qe3+ { . }{ Wherever the king moves, we can play ... h5 !? with approximate equality. } )
