12. Na2{ Played by Polish GM Krasenkow and has a very ambitious strategy. Perhaps too ambitious! }
12. Nc6
13. Nxb4
13. cxb4{ Krasenkow's opponent recaptured with the knight, but I like this bold recapture more. It's a battle of knights versus bishops now, and one where I feel the knights are in good shape. We have plenty of juicy squares to jump to while the positions remain relatively closed, meaning the bishops aren't too meaningful just yet.    The engine slightly leans towards Black here and I want to emphasize once again just how annoying it is for White to have the pawn on  g4 . If it were on  g2 , we would be evaluating the position differently. }
