11. Bxe4{ A bail-out option. Instead of sacrificing the pawn, more pieces get exchanged. }
11. Bb4( 11...Bxe4 12.bxc3 { gives White something to work with. } )( { Therefore, we chose }11...Bb4 { and shouldn't fear the doubling of the pawns. As we have already seen in other places in this course, the doubled f-pawns often prove very effective. } )
12. Bxf5
12. exf5
13. Bd2
13. Na6{ The position is equal. We can use the half-open e-file for our rook and after an eventual exchange of bishops, our knight will find a great outpost on  d5 . }
