10. Bb7
11. Qh5{ It makes a lot of sense to provoke our g-pawn forward, which weakens the dark squares around our king. }
11. g6
12. Qg4( { Compared to  11.Qg4 , it becomes immediately obvious why }12...h6 13.Ne4 Qd5 { doesn't work here. } )
12. Be7
13. h4{ Played in dozens of games but quite frankly a bad move. It allows us to fall back on a theme we have seen before. }
13. h6
14. Ne4{ Other squares make little sense, as it's only the  e4 -square from which the knight can do some damage on  d6  or  f6 . }
14. Qd5{ Now that  f6  is covered, provoking  f2 - f3  is on the cards once again. }
15. f3
