15. exd5( 15.e5 { isn't great because of }15...Ne4 16.Qxd5 Nc5 { and Black should be preferred. } )
15. Bc6( { A tactical solution, making use of the pin. An alternative would be }15...Bb4 { followed by ... O-O . } )
16. Nc3
16. Nxd5{ This just works tactically. }
17. Ne5
17. Nxc3( 17...Nb4 18.Qxd8+ Rxd8 19.Rxa5 O-O { shouldn't be very worrying either. } )
18. Qxc3
18. Be4{ The next few moves are forced. }
19. Bb2
19. O-O{ No need to fear any discovered attack by the knight: we will always answer with ... Bf6 ! }
20. Nd7
20. Bf6
21. Nxf6+
21. Qxf6{ After capturing on  f6  twice, the endgame is equal. }
