7. Nc3( 7.Bb5+ Nc6 8.Bd2 e6 { transposes to the  7.Bd2 line . } )
7. e6
8. Bd2
8. Nc6
9. Rc1{ White's play feels a bit slow. Our next move takes away the  b5 -square, after which it feels like White's setup just failed. }
9. a6( 9...Be7 { is fine as well as practice has shown. } )
10. Ne5( { By far the most popular move, but a very risky one. White is falling behind in development. Wiser is }10.Nh4 { , after which }10...Be4 11.f3 Bg6 { is approximately equal. } )
10. Bd6
11. f4{ Securing the knight on  e5  but also weakening the  e4 -square for the remainder of the game. }
11. O-O
12. Be2
12. Rfc8
13. O-O
13. Qe7{ Getting out of the gaze of the  c1 -rook. All our pieces are in good positions and, not surprisingly, the engine already gives us an edge. }
