6. Bg6( { I prefer this over }6...Bxd3 7.Qxd3 { , which seems to fall into White's plans somewhat. } )
7. Ne5
7. Bxd3( 7...Nbd7 8.Nxg6 hxg6 { transposes to the  6.Nh4 variation , but there we meet   }8.Bd3 { with }8...c5 { instead of }8...Nbd7 { . On top of that, there is no need to go for this: }{ taking on  d3  is easier. } )
