23. dxe4
24. Rf7
24. Bxc5( { After }25.Rxg7 { , we are two pawns up, but White's activity and g-pawn compensate for it. The engine points at equality after }25...Kc7 26.Bc3 Kd6 27.g6 b5 28.b4 Be3 29.Rh7 Bg5 30.g7 Bf6 31.Kc2 Ne5 32.Bxe5+ Kxe5 33.Bf7 Bxg7 34.Rxg7 c5 35.bxc5 Rxc5+ 36.Kd2 Rc7 37.Rh7 Kd4 { . This line isn't forced but is a pretty realistic scenario. We give back some material to stop the g-pawn but have plenty of pawns to compensate for it. } )
