12. Bxc4
12. c5{ Three correspondence games went down this path. White now needs to deal with the positional threat of receiving an isolated d-pawn. }
13. a3
13. cxd4
14. exd4( { White can't take the bishop pair as }14.axb4 dxc3! 15.Bxc3 axb4 16.Rxa8 Qxa8 17.Bxb4 { loses to }17...b5!  )
14. Bxc3
15. Bxc3
15. O-O
16. O-O
16. Nb6{ This gives us a great outpost on  d5  for the knights. White's bishops can't do much damage here. }
