20. Qd3
20. Bf5
21. Qxf5
21. Qxd4+
22. Kf1{ The win here is far from trivial, but very pretty, so we may as well continue the line a bit longer! }
22. h5{ Preparing to plant a knight on  g4 . }
23. h3( 23.Qc2 Ng4 24.Bxg4 Re1+ { is a key point and similar to the main line. } )
23. h4{ White can barely move. }
24. Qc2
24. Nh5{ Essentially, the same tactic as pointed out on move 23. }
25. Bxh5
25. Re1+
26. Kxe1
26. Qg1+
27. Ke2
