14. O-O{ The most obvious move but not the best! }
14. b5{ This move shows why it is important to play  Rc1  first, when after  Na4 - c5 , a capture on  c5  can be met with  Rxc5 . }
15. Nc5
15. Bxc5
16. dxc5
16. a4{ Gaining more space on the queenside. }
17. Qd3
17. Nc6( 17...O-O 18.c6! { is something to avoid. The knight move is an excellent pawn sacrifice. } )
18. Qxb5
18. O-O{ Black will double on the b-file next and can occasionally play in the center as well with ... e6 - e5 . }
