4. Nh4{ This move is recommended in the fun course  The Killer Colle-Zukertort System  by Simon Williams. }
4. Bg4
5. f3( { Still following Simon's course. Of course, White's point is not to play }5.Be2 { , when Black simply exchanges bishops with a good game. }5.f3 { is certainly more ambitious, but it may not be the best course of action. } )
5. Bd7{ Threatening to win a piece with ... g7 - g5  next, and essentially forcing White's next move. }
6. f4{ White is setting up a Stonewall structure, which can be a very sensible strategy. The Stonewall is the type of setup that requires a bit of knowledge and understanding from the opponent. When the opponent lacks a bit of both, it can be a very successful weapon. }
6. Bg4( { I like this move a lot and believe it is the immediate end of the line. White obviously doesn't want to play }7.Be2 { , as an exchange of bishops would leave a serious hole }{ on  e4 . } )( { If }7.Nf3 { is played though, we continue with }7...e6 { and have managed to get our bishop outside the pawn chain, which is a great achievement. Black holds a positional advantage. } )
