8. Qa5+
9. Nc3
9. O-O-O( { Apparently, }10.Qd3 { is the only move that keeps the balance here, but I think it's unlikely to be played by our opponents. Just in case, we go }10...Bxf3 11.Qxf3 Nxd4 12.Qh3+ Qf5 { and White should be careful not to drift into a worse position. } )
