6. exd4
6. Qb6{ An annoying move to face for White, now that we have included the capture on  d4 . }
7. c4{ The critical move, still fighting for the initiative. }
7. e6{ Renewing the threat to  b2 . The fact that we exchanged on  d4  means that the newly arrived pawn can easily be attacked but a future ... g7 - g5 - g4 , and makes it easy for the  f8 -bishop to slide into the game on  b4 . }( { Objectively, }7...Qxb2 8.cxd5 Qxa1 9.dxc6 { may even be playable for Black, but I just don't like the look of it. White has a large lead in development and such positions are always dangerous. The engine's '0.00' also doesn't give us much to work with. } )
8. Qd2{ A bit artificial, and the queen is vulnerable here as we will see. }
8. g5
9. Bg3
9. Nf6{ The knight is simply aiming for  e4 . Black has a good game. }
