7. O-O
7. O-O{ This is the position we have been aiming for. Our king's position is rock solid and impossible to break. }
8. Qe1{ Played in over 1000 games. The idea is quite simple: White's attacking scheme revolves around bringing the queen to  h4 , bishop to  h6 , and knight to  g5 . When those pieces are in position, tactics involving  Rxf6  will likely be decisive. As usual, that all sounds very good in theory, but in practice we will never allow such things to happen, obviously! }
8. Nc6{ Preparing active counterplay in the center. }
9. Qh4
9. Bg4( { It becomes clear that White's attack is way too slow. The planned }10.Bh6 { loses instantly after we exchange on  h6  and  f3 , followed by ... Qd8xd4 +. } )
