2. a3{ Certainly playable, as demonstrated by the likes of Carlsen and Nakamura. It should be noted though that when they are having their day, I suppose they can make any move look good. }( { If there is any point then, like after  2.c3 , Black is dissuaded from going }2...c5 { here since White can capture that pawn and follow up with  b2 - b4  easily. Instead, we should just focus on healthy development. } )
2. Nf6
3. Nf3
3. e6( { Somewhat surprisingly, our go-to solution with }3...Bf5 { is not that great here because of }4.c4 e6 5.Qb3 { , with pressure. That's why we take play into a different type of London, where the }{ move  a2 - a3  isn't particularly helpful. } )
4. Bf4
